From 578ebb66d9e1d90a58a1204f27bb3408482f90d1 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Esteban Urrutia <esteuwu@proton.me>
Date: Sat, 16 May 2026 13:19:20 -0400
Subject: [PATCH 1/5] arm64: dts: qcom: Initial support for Motorola ThinkPhone
 by motorola (motorola-bronco)

The ThinkPhone by motorola is a smartphone released by Motorola in 2023, based on the Qualcomm Snapdragon 8+ Gen 1 SoC which seems to be in between the SM8450 and SM8550.
The latter fact has made porting certain things.. interesting, to say the least.

What works:
- USB 2.0, USB 3.0 (SuperSpeed Plus Gen2x1)
- UFS
- Battery (battman)
- Display
- Touchscreen
- GPU acceleration
- Camera flash
- Wi-Fi
- Bluetooth
- NFC
- Sensors (SDSP)

For the display, only the NT37703 DriverIC + Tianma panel combination has been tested. I don't have the other combination, which is the VTDR6115 DriverIC + a CSOT panel.
The display currently shows artifacts under some scenarios. DSC is most likely the cause.
Downstream specifies bpp 8 and bpc 10, but that causes the display to just not work.
For Wi-Fi and Bluetooth, calibration files are missing as of now, so the connection range is extremely small.
NFC seems to work? Cards get detected using nfctool but I haven't been able to learn how to read the actual contents of cards using nfctool.
USB dual-role works properly in both speeds, the only missing thing is the retimer driver. The phone can deliver power in host mode which is awesome. Orientation switching works as well.
The retimer driver being missing may be the reason why DP out support is not working.
All sensors (accelerometer, magnetometer, light sensor, proximity sensor, gyroscope and compass) seem to work using hexagonrpcd.
Motorola is to blame for the handover spam in the kernel log.

Audio and everything else is in the works.
The modem seems to be waiting for something else (most likely IPA), even after being given proper firmware and persist files? I'm currently investigating that as well.
